<br>
The Grimoire is a four slot container with a Combine button at the bottom.  You put your components in it (yes, you will need another copy of the previous level's pet spell), click the Combine button, and if successful you will now have a nice new spell scroll on your cursor that you can scribe into your spell book.  Whether the combine is successful depends on your research skill - the higher the better.  If you haven't trained any points in your research skill, then that's probably going to be your biggest problem.  Go to a magician trainer and see if you have any skill points available.  If you do and you haven't put any into research, put as many points as you can into it.  If you don't have any research points available or can't get your research skill high enough to do a successful combine, you can ask a higher level magician with a high research skill to do the combine for you (it's polite to give that magician the elemental grimoire with the components in it and ready to be combined).<br>
<br>
Probably the best source on research was magecompendium, but while that's down goto to eq.castersrealm.com and click the &quot;research&quot; link towards the bottom of the menu on the left for more info (you will also see info on concordance quests that you can do to get your research skill up).  Also, check the bazaar regularly, you can usually buy the required components instead of waiting to loot them from the monsters you kill. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=borbos>Borbos</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 42<br> <font color=#333333>(3/3/03 4:40 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1867.topic&index=2>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Help Lvl32 Mage Do Research for 1st Time?</span><hr size=1> Here is another research link <!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://mythiran.allakhazam.com/">mythiran.allakhazam.com/</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--> Was called mythiran Tower back in the day the be all of research sites now pretty much just information bout basics, don't think its been updated for a long time. Also in the skills section is a thread where mages have put up their server and research skill so you can also take a look at that to help you on your way.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=h